          <msContents>
            <summary>[p]Medical note-book, containing entries on urines, general medical practice, etc.; with a number of receipts, prescriptions and remedies: Written by several hands. 
[p]Ff. 3-33 On urines: in English, arranged by question and answer. 
[p]22v-30 On humours, etc.: in English and Latin. 
[p]31-99 General practice of medicine: in English and Latin. 
[p]101-153 Medical receipts in English. 
[p]154-end Notes on pharmacy, therapeutics, receipts, etc.: in Latin and English. 
[p]The name 'Alleyne' is an uncertain reading. On the verso of the first leaf is an inscription 'master allyns[?] his Booke' and on the second leaf is another inscription 'Philipo alleyno[?] Pastori in andeuera' [Andover?].</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="" source="IANA">English.</textLang>
